        <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> June 2026</p>

        <p>This Cookie Policy is provided pursuant to the Italian Data Protection Authority's decision of 8 May 2014 and subsequent amendments, and describes the use of cookies by <strong>buildhub.it</strong>.</p>

        <h2>1. What cookies are</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files that websites visited by the user send to their device (computer, tablet, smartphone), where they are stored and then retransmitted to the same websites on the next visit. Cookies can perform various functions: enabling efficient browsing, remembering preferences, improving the browsing experience and providing information to the website operator.</p>

        <h2>2. Types of cookies used by this website</h2>
        <p><strong>buildhub.it</strong> exclusively uses the following types of cookies:</p>

        <h3>2.1 Technical cookies</h3>
        <p>These are cookies essential for the proper functioning of the website. They are used to manage browsing, enable the contact form to be sent and ensure connection security. These cookies do not require user consent under current legislation.</p>
        <p>The website is built with static technology (Eleventy static site generator) and does not use dynamic content management systems, databases or server-side sessions: as a result, it does not use persistent session cookies or authentication cookies.</p>

        <h3>2.2 Analytics cookies</h3>
        <p><strong>This website does not use analytics cookies.</strong> No tools such as Google Analytics, Google Tag Manager, Facebook Pixel or other tracking systems are installed. User browsing is not monitored or profiled.</p>

        <h3>2.3 Profiling and marketing cookies</h3>
        <p><strong>This website does not use profiling cookies</strong> or cookies for marketing or behavioural advertising purposes. No tracking pixels, social plugins or retargeting tools are present.</p>

        <h2>3. Third-party services</h2>
        <p>The website uses the following external services that may collect user data (IP address, user agent) for their technical operation:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Fonts</strong> (fonts.googleapis.com, fonts.gstatic.com) — web font service. Requesting fonts involves transmitting the user's IP address to Google's servers. Google does not set cookies for this service. <a href="https://developers.google.com/fonts/faq/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">More information</a>.</li>
          <li><strong>Leaflet interactive map</strong> with CARTO tiles and OpenStreetMap data — map visualisation service. The map loads tiles from <strong>cartocdn.com</strong> and data from <strong>openstreetmap.org</strong>, which receive the user's IP address to deliver content. No cookies are set.</li>
          <li><strong>Nominatim</strong> (geocoding) and <strong>OSRM</strong> (route calculation) — OpenStreetMap services used for the address search functionality on the contact page map. Data entered by the user is transmitted to these services for processing. No cookies are set.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>These services are integrated exclusively for technical purposes and do not involve profiling or tracking of the user. Opening links to external sites, including those of the Data Protection Authority, does not result in the installation of cookies by our website.</p>

        <h2>4. How to disable cookies</h2>
        <p>Since the website uses only essential technical cookies, a cookie consent banner is not required. Should the user nevertheless wish to disable all cookies (including technical ones), they can do so through their browser settings. Below are links to guides for the most common browsers:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Google Chrome:</strong> <a href="https://support.google.com/chrome/answer/95647" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></li>
          <li><strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong> <a href="https://support.mozilla.org/en-US/kb/enable-and-disable-cookies-website-preferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></li>
          <li><strong>Safari:</strong> <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/guide/safari/sfri11471/mac" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></li>
          <li><strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> <a href="https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/microsoft-edge/delete-cookies-in-microsoft-edge-63947406-40ac-c3b8-57b9-2a946a29ae09" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Guide</a></li>
        </ul>
        <p>Please note that disabling technical cookies may impair the proper functioning of the website.</p>

        <h2>5. Changes to this Cookie Policy</h2>
        <p>This Cookie Policy may be subject to changes over time. Users are invited to periodically review this page. The date of the last update is indicated at the top of the document.</p>

